  "defaultMethodClassificationDescription": "Representative farm typologies were used to ensure that results relate to typical UK grazing-based dairy systems, using a variety of sources. Farm structure and inputs (excluding feed) were defined according to the major extensive, pasture-based dairy farm typology identified from statistical anlaysis of 14 years of UK dairy farm statistics (Gonzalez-Mejia et al., 2018). Feeding regime used information from a recent meta-analysis on HSG systems (Foskolos and Moorby, 2017) and outputs from the Cornell Net Carbohydrate and Protein System (CNCPS; Van Amburgh et al., 2015) feed model.",
